const n='---\ntitle: "System Logs API"\ndescription: "Endpoints for managing and retrieving application event logs."\n---\n\n# System Logs API\n\nThis section describes the API endpoints for managing and retrieving system event logs. These endpoints require administrator authentication.\n\n## Admin Endpoints (Requires Authentication)\n\n### List Logs\nRetrieve a paginated list of system logs.\n\n**Endpoint:** `GET /api/admin/logs`\n\n**Query Parameters:**\n- `page` (optional): The page number to retrieve. Defaults to `1`.\n- `pageSize` (optional): The number of logs per page. Defaults to `50`.\n\n**Response:**\n```json\n{\n  "logs": [\n    {\n      "id": 1,\n      "level": "error",\n      "message": "Payment gateway timeout",\n      "details": "{\\"error\\": \\"Connection refused\\", \\"gateway\\": \\"stripe\\"}",\n      "source": "payment",\n      "createdAt": "2024-01-01T12:00:00.000Z"\n    }\n  ],\n  "total": 150,\n  "page": 1,\n  "pageSize": 50\n}\n```\n\n### Delete a Log\nDelete a specific log entry by its ID.\n\n**Endpoint:** `DELETE /api/admin/logs/:id`\n\n**Response:**\n```json\n{\n  "success": true\n}\n```\n\n### Clear All Logs\nPermanently delete all system logs.\n\n**Endpoint:** `DELETE /api/admin/logs/clear`\n\n**Response:**\n```json\n{\n  "success": true,\n  "message": "All logs cleared successfully"\n}\n```';export{n as default};
//# sourceMappingURL=7.logs.mjs.map
